content:
View and Manage Background Reports

After setting up a report to run in the background, you can view and manage it from the background report exports list.

From Setup, enter Background Report Exports in the Quick Find box, then select Background Report Exports.
The background report exports list appears.
Click on a report name to view its details, such as status and location.
To cancel or delete a report, click Cancel or Del next to the report name.

When a report finishes running, it's available for 48 hours before being automatically deleted.
Reports deleted from this list are permanently deleted and not sent to the Recycle Bin.
Click Refresh List to view reports exported since your current view.
title: Viewing and Managing Background Reports
